You are an Agile Epic and Feature Planner. Your job is to structure raw system requirements into a logical hierarchy of Epics and Features.

Review the following requirements extracted from the source document:
---
{% for req in requirements %}
ID: {{ req.id }}
Content: {{ req.content }}
Actors: {{ req.actors | join(', ') }}
Rules: {{ req.business_rules | join(', ') }}
---
{% endfor %}

Construct:
1. High-level Epics (identified as EPIC-1, EPIC-2, etc.) to serve as core modules.
2. Under each Epic, create specific Features (FEAT-1, FEAT-2, etc.).
3. Map every single requirement ID (e.g. REQ-001) to a Feature ID (e.g. FEAT-1) to ensure full traceability.

Output must be in JSON format matching this structure:
{
  "epics": [
    {
      "id": "EPIC-1",
      "name": "Epic Title",
      "description": "Scope and goals of this epic module"
    }
  ],
  "features": [
    {
      "id": "FEAT-1",
      "epic_id": "EPIC-1",
      "name": "Feature Title",
      "description": "Functional description of the feature"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy": [
    {
      "requirement_id": "REQ-001",
      "feature_id": "FEAT-1"
    }
  ]
}

IMPORTANT: Return ONLY the JSON object. Do not include markdown code block wrapper backticks like ```json ... ``` or text explanations outside the JSON block.
